    {
        "id": 33, "title": "Entropy Analysis",
        "description": "Shannon entropy measures randomness. Normal code: ~5-6. Strings: ~4. Encrypted/compressed: ~7.5-8.0. Use entropy to find hidden/encrypted regions.",
        "challenge": "Write calculate_entropy(data: bytes) -> float that computes Shannon entropy in bits.\nH = -Σ p(x) × log₂(p(x)) for each byte value x that appears.",
        "hint": "Count each byte value. p(x) = count(x) / total. entropy = -sum(p*log2(p) for p in probs if p > 0).",
        "solution": "import math\n\ndef calculate_entropy(data):\n    if not data:\n        return 0.0\n    counts = [0] * 256\n    for b in data:\n        counts[b] += 1\n    total = len(data)\n    entropy = 0.0\n    for c in counts:\n        if c > 0:\n            p = c / total\n            entropy -= p * math.log2(p)\n    return entropy\n\ndef find_high_entropy_sections(data, chunk_size=256, threshold=7.0):\n    results = []\n    for i in range(0, len(data), chunk_size):\n        chunk = data[i:i+chunk_size]\n        if len(chunk) >= 64:\n            h = calculate_entropy(chunk)\n            if h >= threshold:\n                results.append((i, len(chunk), h))\n    return results",
        "test_code": "import os\nassert calculate_entropy(b'\\x00' * 100) == 0.0  # all same = 0 entropy\nassert abs(calculate_entropy(bytes(range(256))) - 8.0) < 0.01  # uniform = 8.0\nrandom_data = os.urandom(1000)\nassert calculate_entropy(random_data) > 7.5  # random is near max\nassert calculate_entropy(b'AAAA') < calculate_entropy(b'ABCD')",
        "explanation": "Tools: binwalk -E shows entropy graph. DIE (Detect-It-Easy) plots section entropy. Encrypted shellcode embedded in a binary shows as a high-entropy blob. YARA rule: use pe.sections[i].raw_data_entropy > 7.0.",
        "points": 25, "category": "binary_analysis",
    },
